# Documentation maintenance rules

- When changing project structure, local development workflow, CI stages/jobs, release behavior, repositories, variables, or testing flow, update the relevant documentation in the same task.
- Keep these documents aligned with the actual implementation:
  - `README.md` for quick-start and high-level workflow
  - `README_LOCAL.md` for project structure and local workflow
  - `README_GITLAB_CI.md` for GitLab CI/CD pipeline behavior
  - `.cursor/PROJECT.md` for the agent-facing project overview
- Do not leave documentation updates as an optional follow-up when the change affects documented behavior.
- When appropriate, mention in the final summary which documentation files were updated.